## 4. Auth pattern

| Operation | Identity | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Reads from UC tables | **OBO** (`x-forwarded-access-token`) | UC row filters / column masks / PHI policies apply at query time. |
| Writes to Lakebase (per-app DB) | **App SP** | Apps own their own DB; users do not need direct Postgres roles. |
| Cross-app reference reads | **App SP** with read-only grant on `shared_ref`. | |
| Background jobs / audit log writes | **App SP** | No user context available. |

The dual-mode helpers in `server/auth/` pick the right client automatically:

- `get_obo_client(request)` → user-scoped `WorkspaceClient`
- `get_sp_client()`         → SP-scoped `WorkspaceClient`

