## 5. Governance: what is enforced where

| Concern | Enforced in | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Row-level security on patient/PHI data | **UC** (row filters) | Data must be read via OBO from UC; do not land raw PHI in Lakebase. |
| Column masking | **UC** (column masks) | Same as above. |
| Tag-based policies | **UC** | Lakebase has no equivalent today. |
| Per-app DB isolation | **Lakebase** (one DB per app, SP-scoped role) | Enforced by `apply_grants.py`. |
| Per-user roles inside Lakebase | **App layer** (filter on `x-forwarded-email` / token claim) | Lakebase does not see UC identities natively. |
| Audit log | **Audit middleware** (every request) → `/logz` → Delta sink | See §6. |

### Data classification rule (binding)

> **Sensitive data (PHI/PII/regulated) stays in Unity Catalog and is read on
> behalf of the user.** Lakebase is for app state, derived/aggregated data,
> reference data, and write-back of user actions. Landing sensitive raw data
> in Lakebase bypasses UC governance — do not do it.

The pre-deploy validator does not (cannot) enforce this — it is a review-time
rule. Call it out explicitly in PR descriptions when you land new tables.

